  <h1>Executive Summary</h1>

  <p class="lead">
    bearerCORE&#8482; is a protocol-grade digital currency infrastructure that enables African
    central banks to issue, validate, and settle CBDC banknotes across all 54 sovereign
    corridors of the African Union — without requiring recipients to hold a bank account.
  </p>

  <p>
    Modelled on the physical cash metaphor — where possession equals ownership — bearerCORE&#8482;
    introduces the <strong>CBDC Issuance Bill (CBIB)</strong>: a cryptographically signed digital
    banknote that is minted by a central bank, delivered to commercial banks, and redeemable
    instantly by any holder, anywhere on the continent.
  </p>

  <p>
    Unlike account-based CBDC systems that replicate commercial banking infrastructure,
    bearerCORE&#8482; operates as a <strong>bearer instrument</strong>. A CBIB carries its own
    value, identity, and provenance inside the file itself — enabling offline storage,
    peer-to-peer transfer, and settlement without intermediary custody.
  </p>

